subquestions.solution:
Using the Quadratic Formula $x = \frac{-b \pm \sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}$, we substitute $a = 4$, $b = -3$, and $c = 12$. This gives: 
\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{-(-3) \pm \sqrt{(-3)^2 - 4(4)(12)}}{2(4)} 
&= \frac{3 \pm \sqrt{9 - 192}}{8} 
&= \frac{3 \pm \sqrt{-183}}{8} 
&= \frac{3}{8} \pm \frac{\sqrt{183}}{8}i.
\end{align*}Thus, the solutions are $x = \frac{3}{8} \pm \frac{\sqrt{183}}{8}i.$

Given $a = \frac{3}{8}$ and $b = \frac{\sqrt{183}}{8}$, we calculate $a + b^2$ as follows: 
\begin{align*}
a + b^2 &= \frac{3}{8} + \left(\frac{\sqrt{183}}{8}\right)^2 
&= \frac{3}{8} + \frac{183}{64} 
&= \frac{24}{64} + \frac{183}{64} 
&= \frac{207}{64}.
\end{align*}Thus, $a + b^2 = \frac{207}{64}.$

